item.title: Project fallout v2 update! [lock, update is over]
item.dc:creator: @Javafire Javafire
item.description:
@Javafire wrote:

o rlly he’s 28 years old?
I added an update, construction is now like the old frugooscape version, i created a stable base and only 12 lines of code have been used so far, i will try to get a pic tonight.[br][br][br][br][size=1]Posted on: September 09, 2009, 05:30:55 pm[/size][hr][quote=“Tonic, post:12, topic:300890”][quote author=Javafire link=topic=397175.msg2950192#msg2950192 date=1252453095]
take the gun for example, i added real bullets and made the shooting emote so now it looks like it is shooting a gun, i also added 3d hitmarks instead of the original red and blue ones. your health is no longer above your head but is a bar on the side of your inventory and on the side of your map (you can turn the above head on and off). i added an invisible button that allows your character to be nulled and makes you invisable from everyone but yourself (that part is a little tricky since it doesn’t save any info while you’re nulled). I also added a custom racetrack with peter’s tile editor coords 9999,4003. I added animated npcs that act like they are getting hit by the bullets when you are equiping a gun and such. some of these things are finished some others are not but these are only a fraction of what project fallout has to offer as i said screenshots come out later. the due date for project fallout is 1/22/09.
[/quote]

Pics or video to prove it?[/quote][quote=“Tonic, post:14, topic:300890”][quote author=Javafire link=topic=397175.msg2950380#msg2950380 date=1252460388]
i will release as soon as i finish adding the stuff, and why do people spam and flame to a pointless end, they might as well be saying BAN ME! BAN ME!
[/quote]

I was not flamming you was just asking…[/quote]
i will post the pictures, and i didn’t mean you i ment afernio
